{"from":"manager","to":"eng-1-1","body":"TASK 14: Build scripts/match.py — Stockfish match runner\n\nYou can start this NOW — it doesn't need UCI merged. Build and test with Stockfish vs Stockfish first.\n\nCreate scripts/match.py:\n\nA Python script that plays two UCI engines against each other via subprocess.\n\nRequirements:\n1. Launch engines via subprocess.Popen with stdin=PIPE, stdout=PIPE, stderr=PIPE\n2. Helper functions: send_command(proc, cmd), read_until(proc, keyword) — to communicate UCI\n3. Initialize both engines: send 'uci', wait for 'uciok', send 'isready', wait for 'readyok'\n4. Configure Stockfish: send 'setoption name UCI_LimitStrength value true' and 'setoption name UCI_Elo value 1200'\n5. Play N games (default 20), alternating which engine plays white\n6. Each game:\n   - Send 'ucinewgame' + 'isready' to both\n   - Track moves list, build 'position startpos moves ...' string\n   - Alternate: send 'go wtime 300000 btime 300000' to current side's engine\n   - Parse 'bestmove <uci>' response\n   - Apply move, check for game end (use Board + generate_legal_moves to detect checkmate/stalemate)\n   - 200-move limit for draws\n7. Print per-game results and final W/L/D tally with winrate\n\nUsage: python scripts/match.py --engine1 'python main.py' --engine2 'stockfish' --games 20\n\nTest with: python scripts/match.py --engine1 stockfish --engine2 stockfish --games 2\n(Stockfish vs Stockfish at 1200 ELO to verify the harness works)\n\nMake sure to handle: engine crashes, timeout on bestmove, illegal moves gracefully.\n\nStockfish binary path: just 'stockfish' (it's installed and on PATH).","msg_type":"assign","timestamp":1773175217}